# Backend System Design

## Roles

- super-admin
- admin
- agent

## Role Capabilities

### super-admin

- Manages entire application
- Creates companies and their super-admins
- Views all dashboards
- Manages subscription plans
- Manages billing and revenue

### admin

- Head of a company
- Manages admins
- Sends messages
- Runs campaigns
- Views company dashboard and reports

### agent

- Sends messages
- Runs campaigns

## Customers

- End users of a company

## Core Domains

- companies
- users (admins, agents)
- customers
- groups
- templates
- chats
- campaigns
- workflows
- subscriptions
- billing

## System Characteristics

- Multi-company architecture
- Role-based access control
- Queue-based processing for heavy tasks
- Real-time chat using websockets

## Data & Infra

- PostgreSQL (primary DB)
- Redis (caching + queues)
- S3 (file storage)
- Dockerized services
- Weekly backups

## Performance Goals

- High availability
- Low latency
